TITLE: Target’s earnings take a huge hit as retailer sells off unwanted inventory
SUMMARY: The big-box retailer cut its profit outlook in June, saying it would take a hit as it marked down unwanted goods and canceled merchandise orders.

TITLE: Mortgage demand fell last week even as rates declined slightly
SUMMARY: A small drop in mortgage rates was not enough to fuel any kind of recovery in consumer demand for home loans.

TITLE: Lowe's reports mixed second-quarter results, citing shortened spring that hurt sales
SUMMARY: Lowe's said improved operations offset lower-than-expected sales that were hurt by a shortened spring.

TITLE: Best Buy to sell over-the-counter hearing devices this fall following change in FDA regulation
SUMMARY: Best Buy will begin selling over-the-counter hearing devices as early as mid-October following a new FDA rule.

TITLE: Feds call for water cutbacks 'to avoid a catastrophic collapse' of Colorado River
SUMMARY: The Department of the Interior has called for water cutbacks amid a 23-year drought made worse by high heat and low precipitation brought on by climate change.

TITLE: Monkeypox cases jumped 20% in the last week to 35,000 across 92 countries, WHO says
SUMMARY: Nearly all cases are reported in Europe and the Americas among men who have sex with men, according to WHO.

TITLE: We're making two sales due to an overbought market, meme stock froth
SUMMARY: We're making a couple of small trims Wednesday morning for two reasons.

TITLE: Retail sales little changed in July amid fall in gas prices and drop in auto sales
SUMMARY: Retail activity was flat in July as falling fuel prices held back gas station sales and consumers turned more heavily to online shopping.

TITLE: Drought conditions in Britain prompt water restrictions for millions in London
SUMMARY: The Temporary Use Ban is set to come into effect from August 24.

TITLE: Bed Bath & Beyond surges again on Wednesday, continuing August meme rally
SUMMARY: Bed Bath & Beyond has seen big moves on heavy trading volume as Reddit traders appear to have restarted the meme trade.

TITLE: Dodge's first electrified vehicle will be a new crossover called the Hornet
SUMMARY: The first electrified vehicle for Stellantis' Dodge brand will be a plug-in hybrid crossover called the Hornet, a resurrected name of a 1970s station wagon.

TITLE: Trump-linked SPAC Digital World Acquisition postpones earnings report after seeking to delay merger
SUMMARY: Digital World Acquisition Group, the SPAC that plans to merge with Trump Media and Technology Group, requested a delay in its earnings report.

TITLE: Looking for an offbeat European holiday? This island has its own rules, language and vodka
SUMMARY: Accessible via ferry or flight, Jersey has nearly 50 miles of coastline, more sunshine than mainland U.K. and plenty for travelers to do in the Channel Islands.

TITLE: BlackRock makes $700 million investment in Australian battery storage
SUMMARY: BlackRock says Akaysha has plans to develop energy storage projects in a range of Asia-Pacific markets.

TITLE: Cramer's lightning round: LKQ Corp is a buy
SUMMARY: "Mad Money" host Jim Cramer rings the lightning round bell, which means he's giving his answers to callers' stock questions at rapid speed.

TITLE: Swap speculative stocks for more boring plays even as market rallies, Jim Cramer says
SUMMARY: "It's time to take profits on the most speculative stocks in your portfolio and move that money into something more resilient," the "Mad Money" host said.

TITLE: Jim Cramer warns investors not to bet prematurely on a soft landing
SUMMARY: Jim Cramer issued a warning to fair-weather bulls on Tuesday's episode of "Mad Money."

TITLE: Consumers are expected to have spent slightly more in July, but Prime Day may have boosted sales
SUMMARY: Consumers are expected to have spent just slightly more in July, but they may have boosted what they spent online in a big way.

TITLE: Financing a new car? Here's how much you can save thanks to a good or excellent credit score
SUMMARY: For a five-year, new-car loan of $45,000, buyers with excellent credit scores generally can save thousands of dollars by qualifying for lower interest rates.

TITLE: The Inflation Reduction Act caps costs for Medicare patients on insulin. Where the push for broader relief stands
SUMMARY: The Inflation Reduction Act will limit insulin co-pays for Medicare patients to $35 per month. Where efforts to provide similar relief to other patients stand.

TITLE: Biden signs Inflation Reduction Act into law, setting 15% minimum corporate tax rate
SUMMARY: After more than a year of debate, Biden's sweeping infrastructure bill is became law — albeit a significantly smaller version of his Build Back Better plan.

TITLE: IRS interest rates jump to 6% on Oct. 1. Here’s how much money you’ll get for a missing refund
SUMMARY: If you’re still waiting on a tax refund, you may be earning interest on your unpaid balance, and the rate jumps to 6% on Oct. 1, according to the IRS.

TITLE: Walmart CEO Doug McMillon says even wealthier families are penny-pinching
SUMMARY: Inflation is rising at the fastest rate in decades and groceries, one of the retailer's key categories, have especially jumped in price.

TITLE: Homebuyers are backing out of more deals as high mortgage rates persist and recession fears linger
SUMMARY: Homebuilder cancellation rates have more than doubled since April, according to surveys by John Burns Real Estate Consulting.

TITLE: 'Avatar,' Spider-Man and Star Wars return to the big screen as summer box office winds down
SUMMARY: Disney and Sony are rereleasing "Rogue One," "Spider-Man: No Way Home" and "Avatar" in domestic theaters in the coming weeks.

TITLE: Polestar will launch a hot new electric roadster — but not until 2026
SUMMARY: Polestar said it will build a version of its popular O2 roadster show car. Production won't start until 2026, but interested buyers can reserve now.

TITLE: Walmart sticks with second-half outlook after earnings beat expectations
SUMMARY: The retailer's profits are under pressure, as consumers feel pinched by inflation and buy fewer high-margin items, such as apparel and electronics.

TITLE: American Airlines agrees to buy 20 supersonic planes from Boom
SUMMARY: American Airlines has agreed to purchase 20 supersonic Overture planes from Boom Supersonic, the second firm order for Boom in the last two years.

TITLE: Home Depot beats second-quarter earnings expectations, stands by 2022 guidance
SUMMARY: Home Depot reported second-quarter earnings and revenue that beat expectations Tuesday morning.

TITLE: CNBC Chairman Mark Hoffman to step down in September
SUMMARY: CNBC Chairman Mark Hoffman will step down next month after running the network since 2005.
